Apple of Immunity
Wondrous Item, legendary (requires attunement)

This green magical orb looks like a glass apple ornament. While holding it, you can use your bonus 
action to speak its command word and cause the apple to hover around you. While the apple is 
hovering around you, whenever you take damage, you can use
your reaction to take no damage instead. Once you do, you have immunity to the damage types 
prevented by the reaction until the next dawn. Whenever you are subjected to the said damage type, 
you regain 1d4 hit points instead of taking damage.
Once used, the globe can't be used in this way again until the next dawn.
Chopsticks of Extension
Wondrous item, uncommon
You can use the chopsticks to manipulate creatures from a distance. You can affect creatures within 
300 feet that are also at least 120 feet away from you. As an action, you can use the chopsticks to 
hold a creature and move it. The target must succeed on a DC 10 Strength saving throw or it moves 
10 feet in a direction of your choice. Large creatures have advantage on
this saving throw, and Huge or larger creatures automatically succeed on it.
Cotton Candy Vase
Wondrous Item, common
Foodfolk of Silverplate use this vase both for decorative
and culinary purposes.
When you plant a seed inside, it grows twice as fast as its expected growing speed. The leaves of 
the plants growing inside this vase are cotton candy, although their fruit (if they bear any) is 
ordinary.
Fiery Oven Mitts
Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)
These mitts look like regular oven mitts with red runes on them. When you wear these mitts, you are 
protected from fire. You have resistance to fire damage.
When you make an unarmed attack while wearing the mitts, they blaze with fire and fury. Your 
successful unarmed attacks made with your hands deal an additional 1d6 fire damage.

