Necklace of Temperature
Wondrous Item, very rare (requires attunement)
This golden necklace decorated with rubies and sapphires is crafted to protect the wearer against 
extreme temperatures. While wearing the necklace, you are immune to being burnt or frozen (p. 47). 
Also, when you take fire or cold damage, you can choose to end the necklace's immunity effects and 
negate the damage as
a reaction. If you do so, the necklace loses its magical properties until the next dawn.
Pomegrenade
Wondrous item, uncommon
As an action, you can throw this pomegranate-shaped grenade up to 30 feet, causing it to explode 
upon colliding with a solid surface. If there is a creature at the point of impact, it must make a 
DC 15 Dexterity saving throw, taking 8d6 thunder damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on 
a successful one. After the first explosion, thousands of little pomegrenades spawn from the bigger 
one and fly toward the adjacent spaces. Each creature within 10 feet of the explosion (except the 
one at the impact point) must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw, taking 12d4 thunder damage on a 
failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. This item is destroyed after it explodes.
Robe of Napkins
Wondrous Item, rare (requires attunement)
This soft, white robe is designed to protect its wearer against unwanted accidents. While wearing 
this robe, any damage you take is dealt to the robe instead. The robe of napkins has 20 hit points, 
resistance to cold damage, and vulnerability to fire damage. When its hit points are reduced to 0, 
the robe withers away and
reappears on you at the next dawn. Any excess damage
carries over to you.

Sprinkles of Wayfinding
Wondrous Item, uncommon

This small pouch contains 1d4 + 4 pinches of colorful magical sprinkles. You can use an action to 
scatter a pinch in front of you and speak the name of a place. The magical sprinkles form a line in 
the air leading to the named location. If there are multiple places with the same name, the 
sprinkles form a path toward the closest one. A single pinch can only form a 10-mile line. If the 
place is protected against divination spells such as the nondetection spell or is located in a 
different plane of existence than the one you are currently in, the scattered sprinkles fall to the 
ground and don't show a path. The magical line created by the sprinkles disappears after a day.

Strawberry of Resistance
Wondrous Item, uncommon (requires attunement)

At first glance, this magical red orb looks like a glass strawberry ornament. When you become 
attuned to it, it starts to hover around you and protect you against a single type of damage. 
Whenever you take damage, you can use your reaction to halve the damage. Once you do, you have 
resistance to one of the damage types (of your choice) that were halved by the reaction for the 
next hour.
Once used, the globe can't be used in this way again until the next dawn.
Sugarwater Incense
Wondrous Item, rare
Made of herbs, spices, and pine-wood powder that has been soaked in Sugarwater Run (p. 113) for a 
year and dried, this item is considered sacred by the pilgrims of Silverplate.
The incense itself is black; however, its sweet- smelling smoke has a soft pink color. When it is 
ignited, it creates a 20-foot-radius sphere of smoke centered
on the burning incense. The sphere spreads around corners and lasts for 1 hour.
Creatures who are exposed to the smoke for 1 minute must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving 
throw or be affected by it. A creature may also willingly choose to be affected by the incense.
Affected creatures are immune to being charmed or frightened. Whenever an affected creature tries 
to deal damage, it must roll a d100. On a result of 51-100, the creature cannot take the action and 
its turn ends. Affected creatures have a +2 bonus to Wisdom checks.
The effects end on a creature if it moves out of the area, or when the incense burns out at the end 
of 1 hour. If a creature succeeds on the saving throw, it is
immune to the incense for the next 24 hours.
Sundae Cherry Piece
Wondrous item, artifact

The cherry on top of the Sundae Mountain (p. 136) is a magical mystery placed upon the summit by 
the victorious sundae rebels. Its origin and the methods
of its transportation to the highest peak are unknown. One bite from the enormous cherry is rumored 
to bestow eternal life and wisdom.
The sundae cherry piece can't be targeted by any divination magic or perceived through magical 
scrying sensors.
It takes 5 bites to consume one piece in its entirety. A creature gains the following features 
according to the number of bites it takes from the sundae cherry:
One Bite. All ability scores of the creature increase by 2, up to a maximum of 22.
Two Bites. The creature becomes immortal. It doesn't age and can't be aged magically.
Three Bites. The creature becomes immune to being charmed, frightened, and petrified, and it has 
immunity to all diseases.
Four Bites. The creature doesn't need to eat, drink, sleep, or breathe.
Five Bites. The creature dies and its body is destroyed. It can't be brought back to life by any 
means. Its soul is trapped within the cherry, the missing parts of which reappear at the top of 
Sundae Mountain.

War Chef’s Apron
Wondrous item, very rare (requires attunement)
While you are wearing this magical white apron, you gain the following benefits:
•  You have proficiency with kitchen weaponry.
•  You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with kitchen weaponry.
•  Your successful melee weapon attacks made with kitchen weaponry deal an extra 2d6 damage of one 
of the following damage types of your choice: acid, cold, fire, or poison.

Wet Wipes
Wondrous item, uncommon
This item is found in magical boxes that each contain 1d8 + 2 wet wipes. You can pull out a wet 
wipe from its box as part of your movement, and once it's taken out of the box, it loses its 
magical properties at the end
of an hour, becoming an ordinary wipe. As an action, you can use a wet wipe to clean a Medium or 
smaller foodfolk corpse, which immediately destroys the
corpse, turning it into a stain on the wet wipe.

